newsArray.title: Smriti Mandhana goes on celebration spree after picking her first wicket in international cricket | WATCH
newsArray.description: India's vice-captain Smriti Mandhana is having a great time on the field in the ongoing ODI series against South Africa. She scored a century in the series opener and then again crossed the 100-run mark in the second game to become the first Indian cricketer in Women's cricket to score a ton in successive ODI innings. Moreover, she came on to bowl for the first time in her international career and struck off the very second ball much to the delight of the crowd.
